  <prompt>
    Build `ClauseComparisonHandler` â€” a pure-deterministic `IToolHandler` implementation
    per FR-16 that performs text-diff with structural awareness on contract clauses.
    Input: two clause texts (e.g., `clauseA` + `clauseB`) plus optional structural hints
    (sentence-level vs paragraph-level vs token-level granularity). Output: structured
    diff report â€” segments added, segments removed, segments unchanged, segments modified;
    plus a normalized similarity score (0.0â€“1.0). NO LLM call. NO Azure OpenAI dependency.
    Uses well-known diff algorithm (Myers or patience diff) on tokenized + normalized
    text.

    "Structural awareness" means: ignores cosmetic whitespace differences; preserves
    sentence boundaries in the segment output; can be configured to group by paragraph
    vs sentence vs word via `sprk_configuration`. Casing-sensitivity, punctuation-sensitivity,
    stop-word handling all configurable.

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100's contract â€” implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "ClauseComparisonHandler"`; lives in
    `Services/Ai/Handlers/ClauseComparisonHandler.cs`. Requires corresponding
    `sprk_analysistool` row with `sprk_handlerclass = "ClauseComparisonHandler"`.

    Tests: contract test + positive cases (identical clauses â†’ similarity 1.0 + all
    unchanged; single-sentence change â†’ only that sentence in modified set; reordered
    paragraphs detected as moves not delete+add) + error cases (empty clause, exceeds
    max length) + config-driven test (granularity setting changes diff output
    deterministically).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + text-diff algorithm experience. Familiar with
    Myers diff, longest-common-subsequence, tokenization strategies, and the legal-domain
    constraints (cosmetic vs substantive change distinction).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ClauseComparisonHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`; auto-discovered;
    `sprk_analysistool` row deployed; unit tests cover positive + error + config-driven
