  <context>
    <background>
      `ClauseComparisonHandler` supports the legal-review workflow where a reviewer
      compares a proposed clause vs the original (or a standard template). Because the
      math is deterministic, reviewers + auditors can replay the diff and get identical
      output â€” important for litigation defensibility.

      Distinct from LLM-assisted `ClauseAnalyzerHandler` (task 106) which STRUCTURES a
      single clause into a typed schema. This handler simply compares two clause texts.
    </background>
